This tutorial explains how this project works:
http://blog.jayway.com/2011/03/02/neo4j-rb-1-0-0-and-rails-3/


To run this project, you should follow these steps:

=> Install Java 1.6

=> Install rvm
https://rvm.beginrescueend.com/

=> Update your RVM
rvm get head

=> Install JRuby:
rvm install jruby-1.6.0

=> Use JRuby
rvm jruby

=> Get this project
git clone git@github.com:lucascaton/testing_neo4j.git

=> Enter in this project directory
cd testing_neo4j

=> Install / run bundler
gem install bundler
bundle

=> Start the server
rails server
